title: In celebration of Lady Gaga’s birthday, here are 20 of her most iconic beauty looks
text:
In celebration of Lady Gaga’s birthday, here are 20 of her most iconic beauty looks Stefani Joanne Angelina Germanotta or rather Lady Gaga is celebrating her birthday today ! This might be Mother Monster’s strongest year yet , as she has almost sold out her tour that doesn’t even kick off until August! Not to mention, she performed at the Super Bowl and is headlining Coachella in place of Beyoncé . After making her name with a handful of iconic albums and performances, she made the jump to television last year with a starring role in American Horror Story: Hotel . She played a vampire, which is fitting because she doesn’t seem to age AT ALL. 
From runways to red carpets, Lady Gaga is as beautiful as ever. In celebration of her birthday, here is a look back at 20 of her best beauty looks.
1. Her red hot smoky eye lewk at this year’s Grammy Awards. Phil McCarten / Getty Images 
2. Her Vintage Hollywood style for the Academy Awards. 
Jason Merritt /Getty Images 
3. Her out-of-this-world yellow Grammy lewk. 
Jason Merritt / Getty Images 
4. This bejeweled ’60s look! 
Kevin Mazur / Getty Images 
5. Her Poker Face look that we all tried recreating. 
6. Her blunt bangs and orange glossy lips for TRL. Scott Gries / Getty Images 
7. Her vampy makeup for an Oscars party. 
Pascal Le Segretain / Getty Images 
8. This timeless cat-eyeliner and coral lip for a Harpers Bazaar party. 
Taylor Hill / Getty Images 
9. Her patriotic look…and all of that glitter. 
Matt Cowan / Getty Images 
10. Her Gwen Stefani ’90s gem brow tribute. Kris Connor / Getty Images 

11. That one time she rocked a bow made from her hair. Charles Eshelman/FilmMagic 
12. When she made this liner makeup look a new trend. 
Marc Piasecki / Getty Images 
13. Her colorful makeup look that we instantly wanted to copy. 
Venturelli/WireImage 
14. This mermaid-worthy cool silver look. 
Jason Merritt / Getty Images 
15. This Marilyn Monroe-inspired red carpet style. 
Kevin Winter / Getty Images 16. When she made a studded mask look really cool. Dimitrios Kambouris/WireImage for Marc Jacobs 
17. Her David Bowie Grammy Awards tribute! 
VALERIE MACON/AFP/Getty Images 
18. When we tried really hard to copy this angelic look that had an edgy twist to it. 
Stephen Lovekin / Getty Images 
19. All of her iconic looks in the “Alejandro” music video. 
20. Her glam, high ponytail day-off look. James Devaney / Getty Images Lady Gaga is a beauty chameleon. From out-of-this-world gems and colors to classic old Hollywood glamour she can truly pull off any style and look gorgeous no matter what![/subheader]
